      <description><![CDATA[
<h2>Notiqflow 0.4.2</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Far fewer correction prompts.</strong> The "Always change…?" card no longer appears for capitalization-only edits (like "trenches" → "Trenches") — those are sentence context, not dictation errors. Prompts are now reserved for genuinely niche words: terms the dictionary doesn't know, misrecognitions being fixed, brand-style casing like "SaaS" or "iPhone", or a fix you've made twice. Everyday one-off edits stay silent.</li>
</ul>
      ]]></description>
